## Step 6: Add Simple Psychological Safety Exercises

Tiny rituals done regularly beat one‑off workshops. [web:219][web:224][web:227][web:230]

Try:

- Red / Amber / Green check‑ins:
  - Quick round at retro start: “Red = overwhelmed, Amber = stretched, Green = OK.” No pressure to explain, but it sets context. [web:219][web:227]
- “One thing I appreciate / one thing I need”:
  - Each person shares one thing they appreciated from the team recently and one thing that would help them work better. [web:227][web:230]
- Monthly micro‑survey:
  - 3–5 anonymous questions like:
    - “On this team I can admit mistakes without fear.”
    - “I feel safe speaking up with concerns.”
  - Track trends rather than obsessing over single scores. [web:227][web:230]

Use the results to tweak how you run meetings, reviews, and incidents; share what you’re changing so people see their input matters. [web:219][web:227][web:230][web:231]

